article.headline: Hampton 30, Florida A&amp,M 15
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Jeremy Gilchrist scored two punt returns to lead Hampton to a 30-15 win over Florida A&M on Saturday. The Pirates (6-4, 5-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) trailed 3-0 most of the first quarter before Gilchrist's 86-yard punt return with 2:14 left in the first. Wesley Taylor kicked a 25-yard field goal for the Rattlers (3-7, 2-5) early in the second to put Florida A&M within 7-6. Ernie Lomax scored on a 1-yard pass from T.J. Mitchell, Gilchrist had a 57-yard punt return and Carlo Turavani kicked a 43-yard field goal to put Hampton up 23-6 at the half. Despite the Rattlers putting the game at 23-15 with five minutes to play, Kevin Beverly scored a 2-yard TD run with 38 seconds remaining to add to the Pirates' tally.
